## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="fe136-111">O exemplo a seguir usa o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> elemento para criar listas de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> elementos que contém os nomes de país, de qualquer um dos quais pode ser usado para reconhecer que o contém frase.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-111">The following example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> element to build lists of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> elements containing country names, any one of which may be used to recognize the containing phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fe136-112">O exemplo, em seguida, adiciona um dos resultante <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objetos para suas respectivas regras para países da Europa e América do Sul países.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-112">The example then adds one of the resulting <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects to their respective rules for European countries and South American countries.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fe136-113">Além disso, o exemplo usa o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objeto às referências de regra de grupo para `ruleEurope` e `ruleSAmerica` em uma lista das duas alternativas, deles de que pode ser usado para reconhecer a entrada de fala.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-113">Further on, the example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to group rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` into a list of two alternatives, either one of which may be used to recognize spoken input.</span></span>  
  
```  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="fe136-116">O exemplo a seguir cria uma gramática que reconhece a frase "uma nação que ganhou a Copa do mundo é" seguido do nome de um país que ganhou a Copa do mundo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-116">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fe136-117">Ele cria uma regra pública denominada `WorldCupWinner`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-117">It creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fe136-118">Em seguida, cria dois <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objetos usando <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objetos que contêm matrizes de novos <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-118">It then creates two <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objects using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects that contain arrays of new <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fe136-119">Para ver a gramática que este exemplo gera, consulte <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-119">To see the grammar that this example generates, see <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
 public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="fe136-124">O exemplo a seguir cria uma gramática que reconhece a frase "uma nação que ganhou a Copa do mundo é" seguido do nome de um país que ganhou a Copa do mundo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-124">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fe136-125">O exemplo usa o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> elemento para criar listas de nomes de país aceitável de uma matriz de <xref:System.String> objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-125">The example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> element to build lists of acceptable country names from an array of <xref:System.String> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fe136-126">O exemplo, em seguida, adiciona um dos resultante <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objetos para suas respectivas regras para países da Europa e América do Sul países.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-126">The example then adds one of the resulting <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects to their respective rules for European countries and South American countries.</span></span>  
  
```  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
    // Create a grammar from an SRGSDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument srgsGrammar = new SrgsDocument ();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule ("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add (new SrgsItem ("A nation that has won the world cup is"));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf (new string[] {"England","France","Germany","Italy"});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf (new string[] {"Argentina","Brazil","Uruguay"});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the grammar and make winnerRule  
  // the root rule of the grammar.  
  srgsGrammar.Rules.Add (new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  srgsGrammar.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="fe136-131">O exemplo a seguir cria uma gramática que reconhece a frase "uma nação que ganhou a Copa do mundo é" seguido do nome de um país que ganhou a Copa do mundo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-131">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fe136-132">O exemplo usa o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objeto para criar listas de nomes de país aceitável de uma matriz de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-132">The example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to build lists of acceptable country names from an array of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fe136-133">Usando o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf.Add%2A> método, o exemplo anexa um <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> que contém a cadeia de caracteres "Itália" para o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objeto `oneOfEurope`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fe136-133">Using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf.Add%2A> method, the example appends an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> that contains the string "Italy" to the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object `oneOfEurope`.</span></span>  
  
```  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany")});  
  oneOfEurope.Add(new SrgsItem("Italy"));  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```
